  <description><![CDATA[<p>La Villa, in the Trentino-Alto Adige region of Italy, is situated at the foot of the Sassongher Mountain linking with the Dolomites’ famous Sella Ronda ski circuit. Located between <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Corvara</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/aa3c7a33c713409b8cca203164e09aca" href="/{localLink:umb://document/aa3c7a33c713409b8cca203164e09aca}" title="San Cassiano">San Cassiano</a>, it is one of the main ski villages in the region of Alta Badia - a UNESCO world heritage site. Every December La Villa hosts the Alpine Ski World Cup on the Gran Risa slope - one of the most technically difficult slopes of the entire Alpine area. La Villa has a grand tradition of welcoming skiers from all over the world, and is known for first class gastronomy and traditional Ladino mountain culture. At the centre of the village there is a range of shops, bars and restaurants. The main language is Ladin – a throwback to Roman times when Latin and a local dialect merged. But don’t worry – English is widely spoken.</p>]]></description>
