  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners</strong> limited skiing for beginners however once you have spent a few days in ski school there are plenty of blue runs over on the Corvara side of the ski area to strech legs and enjoy</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates</strong> a paradise for intermediate skiers who can choose between just skiing the lcoal area of Alta Badia or taking on the challenge of skiing the Sella Ronda from Corvara either clockwise of anti clockwise where there is a host of satisfying red runs</p>
<p><strong>Advanced</strong> Confident skiers have a range of mountains to ski over 1.220km piste. Spend a day over in Selva Where you will find Steep runs to keep you occupied and challenged.  Off piste Cortina and the Hidden Valley are a must.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarders</strong> Will love the snowpark Alta Badia at the Piz Sorega Plateau between the slopes "La Freina" and "Ciampai" with boardercross, rails and jumps to suit your level.</p>]]></generalInformation>
